"```sql\nSELECT d.forename, d.surname\nFROM qualifying q\nJOIN races r ON q.raceId = r.raceId\nJOIN circuits c ON r.circuitId = c.circuitId\nJOIN drivers d ON q.driverId = d.driverId\nWHERE r.year = 2008\n  AND c.name = 'Marina Bay Street Circuit'\n  AND q.q3 = (\n    SELECT MIN(q3)\n    FROM qualifying\n    WHERE raceId = r.raceId\n  );\n```\nThis SQL query retrieves the full name (forename and surname) of the driver who ranked 1st in the 3rd qualifying session (Q3) for the race held at the Marina Bay Street Circuit in 2008. It uses a subquery to find the minimum Q3 time for the specified race, ensuring that the driver with the fastest Q3 time is selected."